<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hello, I have this option in <code>early-init.el</code> which starts the Emacs frame maximized:</p> <pre><code>(push &#39;(fullscreen . maximized) default-frame-alist) </code></pre> <p>However, when I run Emacs in daemon mode and I connect with <code>emacsclient -c</code> there might be some very short delay until the Emacs frame is maximized because <code>mu4e-headers</code> calculate the <code>mu4e-headers</code> using the small window size which I don&#39;t want. I want it to be calculated using the maximized window size</p> <pre><code>(use-package mu4e-headers :ensure nil :after mu4e :custom (mu4e-headers-auto-update t) (mu4e-headers-fields `((:human-date . 12) (:flags . 6) (:from . 22) (:subject . ,(- (window-body-width) 50))))) </code></pre> <p>Is there any other variable like <code>window-body-width</code> that uses the width of the maximized window?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/zoliky"> /u/zoliky </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wb37s6/mu4eheader_view_calculate_windowbodywidth_after/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wb37s6/mu4eheader_view_calculate_windowbodywidth_after/">[comments]</a></span>